<p>Blige gushed: 'Puff has been in my life since the beginning of my career. We were working on What's the 411 together. He was the A&amp;R for my first album. He was already my brother and my family by the time I got the My Life album'</p>

<p>The Bronx-born R&amp;B belter recounted how she was discovered by Uptown Records founder Andre Harrell in 1989 after hearing her cover of Anita Baker's 1986 song Caught Up in the Rapture she recorded at Galleria White Plains.</p>

<p>'[Andre] was like, "Oh my God, you're a star!"' said Mary, who got a house call from Harrell.</p>

<p>'He told my mother, "Your daughter is going to sing for royalty one day." He came to my hood, and heard this young girl sing, and gave me a chance, and everything else was history.'  </p>

